{{`wstar_file` already acts as the opt-in. It is only ever injected by `write_generated_configs`
in the slurm script, so any generic/non-binary `MakeBlobs` run simply won't have the key and
the `if wstar_file is not None:` guard skips all computation. The data loader doesn't have
access to the diagnostics yaml without extra plumbing, which isn't worth it for one cheap numpy
matmul. The two-gate design (data config `wstar_file` + diagnostics `wandb_wstar_acc`) is
sufficient: the computation only runs for binary blobs runs, and logging only happens when the
diagnostics flag is set.}}

